history.content:
When I was studying for 16B after taking 54 (also skipped 16A), I watched all of the circuits lectures and skimmed through the notes for module 3. I think 16A and 16B have become more ML oriented since I studied the material, so I would recommend at least trying to understand Module 3 material; it will show up in the latter part of 16B and in the rest of your EE career, but I didn't suffer in 16B with my more shallow Module 3 knowledge (although the first assignment - redoing the 16A final - was tougher :))

Also you can only skip 16A if you're L&S.

I heard that if you don’t take 16a, but do math 54 instead, then you can take 16b as long as you self-study circuit material in between. Although, the circuit material only comprises 1/3 of ee16a, because another 1/3 is dedicated to machine learning. If I’ve already learned the circuit material (including NVA, capacitance and op-amps) then do I need to study the machine learning lectures too? Or can I go straight to 16B?
history.subject: 16B after Math 54
